modules.description: Provides custom literal syntax for parsing and constructing complex data types such as regular expressions, SQL queries, and SMILES chemical structures. Supports pattern matching on these custom literals, enabling direct manipulation of structured data within expressions. Enables seamless integration of domain-specific notations into Reason code for improved readability and expressiveness.

Processes OCaml AST structures by expanding embedded literals, transforming expressions through a mapping function, and applying a custom expansion pass. Operates on Parsetree.structure and Locmap data structures to modify code during preprocessing. Used to inject or rewrite specific syntax elements in parsed OCaml code.
